reviews.text:
The only thing I noticed is that its missing that toasty flavor. The rice is too fresh &amp; moist.  I wonder if adding popcorn (though I've never used that flavor) to the mix, just a touch, to POP that rice... or something toasted that wouldn't over power the delicacy of the green tea.  By the way have you tried DoMatcha brand genmaicha? try it if you haven't, you'll never drink anything else ;)&#xD;
&#xD;
I love the Tea-Lore of this tea about the servant named Genmai who stole a pocketful of rice &amp; dropped a few grains into the the cup of the samauri lord as he served them their morning tea during a war campaign meeting.  He was instantly beheaded for the insult before the lord drank the tea anyways (as it was a luxury not to be wasted) and liked the roasted flavor so much he named it genmaicha to honor of his late servant. &#xD;
&#xD;
Nice to see other tea fans here, I also adore genmaicha.  Its by far one of my favs. (and I makes teas/tisanes for a living as well as owning an apothecary/clinical practice so that says much!)
